I tried [this code](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=a4bef7ee4bc3530ae34395c28def8140):

```rust
pub struct BoundedVec<T, const S: u32>(Vec<T>);

trait Foo {
    const N: u32;
    fn foo() -> BoundedVec<u8, Self::N>;
}
```

I expected to see this happen: It was a bit unexpected because [this code](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=9f46e37390f9ee4b7b1c5aaecabf5d92) is working fine
```rust
#![allow(incomplete_features)]
#![feature(generic_const_exprs)]

trait Foo {
    const N: usize;
    fn foo() -> [u8; Self::N];
}

struct Data();

impl Foo for Data {
    const N: usize = 7;
    
    fn foo() -> [u8; Self::N] {
        [0; Self::N]
    }
}

fn main() {
    println!("{:?}", Data::foo());
}
```

Instead, this happened: 
```
error[[E0747]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/error-index.html#E0747): type provided when a constant was expected
 [--> src/main.rs:8:32
](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021#)  |
8 |     fn foo() -> BoundedVec<u8, Self::N>;
  |                                ^^^^^^^
  |
help: if this generic argument was intended as a const parameter, surround it with braces
  |
8 |     fn foo() -> BoundedVec<u8, { Self::N }>;
  |                                +         +
```

